<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[135,776,1373,1749]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,247,1373,1397]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
A genus of mostly large hermit crabs found in shallow waters to deeper slopes, and in tropical, subtropical, to temperate latitudes. Forty-four valid species have been described (
<bibRefCitation author="McLaughlin PA &amp; Komai T &amp; Lemaitre R &amp; Rahayu DL" box="[262,550,1469,1493]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="5 - 107" refId="ref45440" refString="McLaughlin PA, Komai T, Lemaitre R &amp; Rahayu DL (2010) Annotated checklist of Anomuran Decapod Crustaceans of the world (Exclusive of the Kiwaoidea and families Chirostylidae and Galatheidae of the Galatheoidea) - part I - Lithodoidea, Lomisoidea and Paguroidea. In: Low MEY &amp; Tan SH (eds.) Checklists of Anomuran Decapod Crustaceans of the world (Exclusive of the Kiwaoidea and families Chirostylidae and Galatheidae of the Galatheoidea) and Marine Lobsters of the World. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 23: 5 - 107." type="journal article" year="2010">McLaughlin et al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu DL" box="[565,729,1469,1493]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="627 - 635" refId="ref47268" refString="Rahayu DL (2010) A new species of Dardanus Paul'son from the Southwestern Pacific (Decapoda, Anomura, Diogenidae). In: Fransen CHJM, De Grave S &amp; Ng PKL (eds.) Studies on Malacostraca: Lipke Bijdeley Holthuis Memorial Volume. Crustaceana Monographs, 14: 627 - 635." type="journal article" year="2010">Rahayu, 2010</bibRefCitation>
), of which 30 are found in the Indo-West Pacific and 12 were previously reported from the 
<collectingCountry box="[460,584,1533,1557]" name="Philippines" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. The PANGLAO 2004 expedition collected 8 of them and added one new record. Moreover, the species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Forskal" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[472,618,1597,1621]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagopodes">
<emphasis box="[472,618,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. lagopodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is determined to be a species complex and is now formally separated into three distinct species, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1824" authorityName="Quoy &amp; Gaimard" authorityYear="1824" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Dardanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolentus">
<emphasis box="[484,679,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">D. sanguinolentus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Quoy JRC &amp; Gaimard JP" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" refId="ref47029" refString="Quoy JRC &amp; Gaimard JP (1824) Zoologie. In: Freycinet LCD de (ed.) Voyage autour du monde sur les corvettes de S. M. l'Uranie et la Physicienne, pendant les annees 1817, 1818, 1819 et 1820. Paris, 1. Pp. 517 - 536." type="journal volume" year="1824">Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1824</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) revalidated and a new species described, thus bringing the total species count in the 
<collectingCountry box="[589,709,1725,1749]" name="Philippines" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Philippines</collectingCountry>
to 15.
</paragraph>
